lead_paragraph: Yelena Isinbayeva of Russia added to her collection of gold medals from major meets yesterday when she won the women’s pole vault at the European Championships in Goteborg, Sweden. Isinbayeva, the reigning Olympic and world champion, cleared 15 feet 9 inches for a meet record, then failed in three attempts to beat her world record of 16 feet 5¼ inches in rainy conditions.
